  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Previous study demonstrated that neuroinflammation induced by surgery is the main cause of
      the postoperative cognitive dysfunction. As an agonist of NMDA receptor, ketamine is proved
      to be an anti-inflammation agent. In present study investigators hypothesized that low dose
      ketamine would prevent the cognition decline after orthopedic surgery in aged patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
